pddl.prompt:
Your name is orchestrator. You are given the public information about the puzzle:
{environment->public_information}
You will receive three structured state reports from the peg agents:
{state_left}
{state_middle}
{state_right}
Your task: integrate these reports and produce a complete PDDL domain and a PDDL problem for the 8-disk Tower of Hanoi suitable for FastDownwards. The domain should define predicates and actions for moving a single disk between pegs while enforcing the rule that a larger disk cannot be placed on a smaller one. The problem should declare all disks and pegs, encode the initial configuration and the goal where the right peg contains all disks in the same top-to-bottom order (A..H). Enclose the domain in <domain></domain> and the problem in <problem></problem>. Precede the PDDL output with a brief note describing any assumptions you made while reconciling the state reports.
